WEBVTT

01:02.271 --> 01:04.272
[shotgun blast]
Shit!

01:21.415 --> 01:22.792
[gunshot]

01:43.979 --> 01:45.981
[gunshot]

01:54.406 --> 01:55.999
[brakes screeching]

01:56.575 --> 01:58.498
Crazy-drivin' motherfucker.

01:59.286 --> 02:00.913
- Shit.
- Come on.

02:03.373 --> 02:06.172
Hey! Hey, Marvin,
what are you doin'?

02:06.376 --> 02:08.628
- He's mine, Jack. Get lost.
- Fuck you he's yours, he's mine.

02:08.836 --> 02:10.589
Eddie assigned this guy to me.
What the hell are you doing'?

02:10.797 --> 02:11.844
Well then go
straighten it out with Eddie.

02:12.007 --> 02:13.054
I'll collect the money.

02:13.258 --> 02:15.135
I almost got killed
tryin' to get this guy.

02:15.344 --> 02:17.142
- He shot at me--
- Back off, goddamn it!

02:17.346 --> 02:18.848
I said I'm takin' him, all right?

02:19.056 --> 02:20.933
- All right, Marvin.
- This guy's worth $1,200!

02:21.141 --> 02:21.892
Okay, okay Marvin.

02:22.100 --> 02:23.818
What the hell are we fightin' for?
We're friends- -

02:24.019 --> 02:26.442
Nothin' personal, Jack,
but fuck off, all right?

02:26.647 --> 02:28.866
Take it easy. Jesus!

02:29.441 --> 02:30.863
Marvin, watch out!

02:32.069 --> 02:34.413
What the fuck's goin' on?
You guys ain't cops.

02:34.655 --> 02:36.498
No, we're ballet dancers.

02:36.907 --> 02:39.660
Didn't your mother ever teach you
how to react to strangers?

02:39.868 --> 02:41.495
Not shoot at them? Huh?

02:56.134 --> 02:58.762
Hey, Marvin, thanks for the car.

02:59.638 --> 03:02.141
You sleep,
and I'll bring it back a little later.

03:03.225 --> 03:04.943
[engine starts]

03:24.371 --> 03:26.339
Got a delivery for you, Gooch.

03:26.748 --> 03:29.467
Jack. The soda machine's been out
for a week and a half.

03:31.837 --> 03:33.305
Check that for me, would ya?

03:33.797 --> 03:35.424
What do we got here?

03:36.800 --> 03:38.017
Alright.

03:38.885 --> 03:41.729
- Give you any trouble?
- Did you give me any trouble?

03:41.972 --> 03:44.020
- Fuck you, man!
- He didn't give me any trouble.

03:44.224 --> 03:45.646
Fuck you, too, man!

03:45.851 --> 03:48.104
- Move!
- I know my motherfuckin' rights!

03:52.232 --> 03:53.484
Slap it.

04:41.531 --> 04:43.659
Moscone's Bail Bonds.

04:46.036 --> 04:49.631
No, it's cash only.
No checks, no cards.

04:50.165 --> 04:54.762
I'm sorry, ma'am. That's the policy.
I wish I could help you out. Sorry.

04:58.215 --> 05:00.058
Just dropped off Bouchet. Is Eddie in?

05:00.258 --> 05:02.477
So you finally caught someone, Jack.

05:02.719 --> 05:04.437
Jerry, is he in?

05:05.013 --> 05:06.640
I think that's terrific.

05:07.349 --> 05:09.317
Jack, I been tryin' to reach
you since last night.

05:09.518 --> 05:10.519
What do you got for me?

05:10.727 --> 05:12.479
Been tryin' to reach me? It's Bouchet.

05:12.729 --> 05:14.606
Ooh, Bouchet. Good score, Jack.
$900, right?

05:14.815 --> 05:15.987
No, it's $1,200.

05:16.274 --> 05:19.244
- No, $900.
- That's, that's $1,200. Come on.

05:19.444 --> 05:21.242
No. Yeah, you're right.

05:22.989 --> 05:24.536
My stomach's killin' me.

05:24.741 --> 05:25.913
<i>I'm gain' over
to Chin Leo's for breakfast.</i>

05:26.117 --> 05:28.870
- I want to talk to you.
- About what?

05:29.746 --> 05:32.499
- I'll talk to you over there.
- Could I have my money first?

05:33.500 --> 05:34.717
Of course.

05:35.043 --> 05:36.636
What, do you think
I'm gonna try and stiff you?

05:36.837 --> 05:38.931
You? Never!
He would never try and stiff me.

05:39.130 --> 05:40.552
Do I detect some kind of sarcasm here?

05:40.757 --> 05:41.679
Never.

05:41.883 --> 05:43.851
Where have
I inherited this reputation?

05:44.052 --> 05:45.850
I have never done business
with anybody,

05:46.054 --> 05:47.271
and Jerry is my witness...

05:47.472 --> 05:49.395
...that I have ever, ever, ever...

05:49.599 --> 05:50.441
Has that phone ever rang...

05:50.642 --> 05:53.236
Has that phone ever rang
with a complaint about me?

05:53.770 --> 05:56.068
Never, never. So let's go.
I'll buy you some breakfast.

05:56.273 --> 05:57.115
I don't eat breakfast.

05:57.274 --> 05:58.901
Well then, have an early lunch.
Let's go.

06:02.779 --> 06:04.781
You ever hear of a guy
named Jonathan Mardukas?

06:04.990 --> 06:07.243
- The Duke. Yeah, I know who he is.
- What do you know?

06:07.450 --> 06:09.327
He's that accountant that
embezzled a couple of million

06:09.536 --> 06:11.379
from some Vegas wise guy
and he gave it to charity.

06:11.580 --> 06:12.422
That's very good.

06:12.622 --> 06:15.876
Only thing is, that it wasn't a couple
of million. It was $15 million.

06:16.042 --> 06:19.012
It wasn't some Vegas wise guy.
It was Jimmy Serrano.

06:20.171 --> 06:22.265
I know, I know.
I can read the papers.

06:22.716 --> 06:25.219
Look, I don't want to
bring up the past, but...

06:26.052 --> 06:27.520
...isn't Serrano the guy
that ran you

06:27.721 --> 06:29.894
out of Chicago when he
was runnin' things back there?

06:30.098 --> 06:31.065
He didn't run me out.

06:31.266 --> 06:34.019
Yeah, right right right. You gave
up bein' a cop to do this shit?

06:35.478 --> 06:37.856
- Alright, what's the point?
- The point, Jack:

06:38.231 --> 06:41.485
I bailed out the accountant.
I didn't know who he was at the time.

06:41.693 --> 06:44.572
I mean, had I known there was
no way I would've put up the bond.

06:44.779 --> 06:46.122
I mean it's only a matter of time

06:46.323 --> 06:48.576
before Serrano vanishes
this guy from the planet

06:48.742 --> 06:50.540
and I'm out $450,000.

06:50.744 --> 06:52.792
You're out $450,000 on this guy?

06:53.038 --> 06:54.130
- No.
- No.

06:54.331 --> 06:56.425
No, because I got you,
and you're the best,

06:56.625 --> 06:58.798
and you're gonna find him
and bring him back.

06:59.002 --> 07:00.299
Yeah, right.

07:00.503 --> 07:02.426
How do you even know
this guy is still alive?

07:02.631 --> 07:06.636
Because this guy is crazy.
He sends postcards to Serrano.

07:06.843 --> 07:09.437
He's tellin' him what a great time
he's havin' with his money.

07:10.513 --> 07:11.890
How much time you got left?

07:12.057 --> 07:14.435
Friday, midnight, I default.
I eat the $450,000.

07:14.643 --> 07:16.645
This Friday? That's five days.

07:16.853 --> 07:19.026
Forget it. You go find him,
give me my money.

07:19.230 --> 07:20.322
Jack, alright, look.
Listen to me.

07:20.523 --> 07:23.117
I'll give you $40...
I'll give you $50,000.

07:23.318 --> 07:26.117
$50,000? I gotta chase you down
for $1,200. Forget about it.

07:26.321 --> 07:29.200
- No, no, no, no, Jack, please.
- Jack, nothing, forget about it. What else you got?

07:29.407 --> 07:30.784
I ain't got nothin', this is it.

07:30.992 --> 07:33.245
If you don't find this guy,
I'm out of business.

07:34.204 --> 07:35.501
Eddie...

07:36.539 --> 07:38.212
I'll do it for $100,000.

07:38.416 --> 07:40.760
$100,000? Are you out of your mind?
This is an easy gig.

07:40.961 --> 07:42.554
It's a midnight run for Chrissakes.

07:42.754 --> 07:45.223
Maybe you haven't noticed,
but I'm tired of gettin' shot at.

07:45.423 --> 07:47.425
I'm tired of this
miserable fuckin' business,

07:47.634 --> 07:48.977
every lowlife that I run into.

07:49.177 --> 07:51.225
If you're gonna pay me,
you gotta pay me what's right.

07:51.429 --> 07:53.852
You want me for this job,
give me what's right.

07:54.057 --> 07:55.980
First of all,
the guy is an accountant.

07:56.184 --> 07:57.401
He's not gonna shoot you.

07:57.602 --> 08:00.321
All you have to do is find him.
You put him in a bag,

08:00.522 --> 08:02.024
hit him with a rubber hose,
bring him home.

08:02.232 --> 08:03.779
That's easy for you to say,
listen to me,

08:03.984 --> 08:07.033
it's $100,000, no more, no less,
and I want a contract.

08:07.237 --> 08:09.831
- Contract?
- That's right, I want it in writing.

08:10.031 --> 08:12.625
$100,000, and I'll have the Duke
here for you by Friday night.

08:12.826 --> 08:14.874
Now, can I have my $1,200, please?

08:18.623 --> 08:21.923
Man, you do worse than any crook
I ever put a bond up for.

08:31.469 --> 08:32.470
Stanley?

08:33.221 --> 08:34.438
Stan.

08:38.018 --> 08:40.191
Hey, Big Dog. How are you?

08:40.937 --> 08:42.405
What are you doin' here?

08:42.605 --> 08:44.107
Listen, I need a favor.

08:44.315 --> 08:47.068
I need to see the booking slip
of a Jonathan Mardukas.

08:47.277 --> 08:49.075
M-A-R-D-U-K-A-S.

08:49.279 --> 08:51.077
There you go.

08:57.454 --> 08:59.923
- Yes, sir.
- What's that?

09:01.750 --> 09:03.969
The number he called
right after he was arrested.

09:06.212 --> 09:07.930
212 area code.

09:08.590 --> 09:10.467
Looks like I'm goin' to New York.

09:17.891 --> 09:19.268
Are you Jack Walsh?

09:21.227 --> 09:22.649
- Excuse me.
- Are you Jack Walsh?

09:22.854 --> 09:25.858
- I'm sorry, do I know you?
- Alonzo Mosely, FBI.

09:26.316 --> 09:29.069
That's a nice badge.
How can I get one of those?

09:29.277 --> 09:30.494
I want to talk to you, Jack.

09:30.695 --> 09:32.413
Yeah? Why don't you
call my social secretary?

09:32.614 --> 09:35.037
Yeah, very funny.
I want to talk to you.

09:35.450 --> 09:37.452
Take your hands off me!

09:40.121 --> 09:41.247
Jeez.

09:41.414 --> 09:42.916
Take it easy!

09:45.960 --> 09:47.587
You know it's a $10 fine
for jaywalking in Los Angeles?

09:47.796 --> 09:48.922
Shut up.

09:49.172 --> 09:50.298
What I want to know is

09:50.507 --> 09:53.761
are you working on anything
having to do with Jonathan Mardukas?

09:54.677 --> 09:56.350
Never heard of him.

09:56.554 --> 09:58.477
Well, I believe you have heard of him.

09:59.891 --> 10:01.438
Let me tell you something, asshole.

10:01.643 --> 10:03.395
We've been working on
this Jimmy Serrano thing

10:03.603 --> 10:05.321
for about six years.

10:05.563 --> 10:07.531
Mardukas is my shot.

10:07.774 --> 10:09.947
I'm gonna bring him into federal court

10:10.151 --> 10:12.028
and I don't want any
third rate rent-a-thug

10:12.237 --> 10:13.955
who couldn't cut it
as a cop in Chicago

10:14.155 --> 10:17.079
bringing him to LA
on some bullshit local charge.

10:26.126 --> 10:27.969
Do I make myself understood?

10:28.503 --> 10:30.130
Can I ask you something?

10:31.256 --> 10:33.429
These sunglasses, they're really nice.

10:33.633 --> 10:34.885
Are they government issued

10:35.093 --> 10:37.767
or do all you guys go to, like,
the same store to get them?

10:41.766 --> 10:43.609
Do I make myself understood?

10:43.810 --> 10:45.437
Can't you take a joke?

10:46.980 --> 10:48.402
Get him out of here.

10:50.108 --> 10:51.234
No, let's talk some more.

10:51.442 --> 10:52.534
Get the fuck out of here.

10:52.735 --> 10:54.408
If I hear anything,
I'll let you know.

10:54.612 --> 10:56.330
Good-bye. Have a nice day.

11:00.326 --> 11:02.124
Think I could have my sunglasses back?

11:02.328 --> 11:03.295
Here's your sunglasses.

11:03.496 --> 11:05.248
[engine revs]

11:07.959 --> 11:11.179
Thanks. Thanks for this, too.

11:15.133 --> 11:16.976
"Alonzo Mosely."

11:17.969 --> 11:19.346
Alonzo.

12:06.392 --> 12:08.019
How's that?

12:08.269 --> 12:10.738
Looks fine to me.

12:11.940 --> 12:13.692
Harold Longman, please.

12:15.652 --> 12:18.451
Harry? Jack Walsh.
How're you doin'?

12:18.655 --> 12:21.750
You got that address check
on that phone number for me?

12:24.244 --> 12:25.416
Uh-huh.

12:25.411 --> 12:29.541
Okay, thanks a lot, Harry.
Say hello to Julie for me. Okay, bye.

12:31.209 --> 12:32.961
Thank you.

12:35.797 --> 12:37.674
You Jack Walsh?

12:39.717 --> 12:41.845
- Who wants to know?
- That's a "Yes."

12:42.262 --> 12:44.014
We'd really like to have
a word with you.

12:44.222 --> 12:47.442
- Yeah? What about?
- It involves big cash, lot of prizes.

12:47.725 --> 12:49.318
I'll make it short and sweet.

12:49.519 --> 12:52.113
The people I work for are really
interested in your visit here.

12:52.313 --> 12:53.781
Oh yeah? Who are the
people you work for?

12:53.982 --> 12:56.360
An old friend of yours
from the Chicago days.

12:57.777 --> 12:58.949
You're here for the Duke.

12:59.153 --> 13:01.201
You think he's in New York,
and we think you're right.

13:01.406 --> 13:03.784
That's a nice jacket.
What is it, goatskin?

13:03.992 --> 13:06.791
Come on, Joey, please. Will you?
Never mind him.

13:07.495 --> 13:08.917
The way I hear it,

13:09.163 --> 13:11.791
you didn't cooperate
with my boss a few years back.

13:11.958 --> 13:13.210
Is that the way you heard it?

13:13.418 --> 13:15.420
Yeah, but I got a
news flash for you, Jack.

13:15.628 --> 13:16.971
He'd pay a hell of a lot more
for the Duke

13:17.130 --> 13:18.473
than that putz bail bondsman
back in LA.

13:18.673 --> 13:21.472
- Oh yeah? How much more?
- How about a one with six zeros?

13:24.345 --> 13:25.813
Are you gonna propose?

13:26.180 --> 13:27.147
- Propose?
- Propose.

13:27.348 --> 13:28.725
'Cause if you're not,
quit starin' at me.

13:28.933 --> 13:30.105
- Okay?
- Starin' at you?

13:30.310 --> 13:32.483
- You're staring at me.
- Joey, back off, will you please? C'mon.

13:32.687 --> 13:36.783
Mr. Walsh, your car's located
in space number 206.

13:36.983 --> 13:39.532
You can catch our shuttle bus
just through these doors.

13:39.527 --> 13:40.198
Thank you.

13:40.194 --> 13:42.913
Here's my number, Jack.
Ask for Tony Darvo. That's me.

13:43.114 --> 13:44.957
They'll put you through
to wherever I am.

13:45.116 --> 13:47.665
And be good to
yourself this time. Okay?

13:51.331 --> 13:53.129
Tell Jimmy I said hello.

14:25.990 --> 14:27.537
[phone ringing]

14:28.868 --> 14:30.996
- [Woman]: Hello?
- Hello? Mrs. Nelson?

14:31.204 --> 14:32.171
<i>Yes</i> g

14:32.372 --> 14:33.965
Alonzo Mosely,
Federal Bureau of Investigation.

14:34.207 --> 14:36.881
- How are you this afternoon?
- I'm fine.

14:37.085 --> 14:39.588
Let me get right to the
point if I may, Mrs. Nelson.

14:39.796 --> 14:42.265
An agent in our Los Angeles office
discovered a detail

14:42.465 --> 14:44.217
that was somehow overlooked until now.

14:44.425 --> 14:46.473
It seems that when a
Jonathan Mardukas was arrested

14:46.677 --> 14:50.102
you were the first person he called.
Is that correct, Mrs. Nelson?

14:51.599 --> 14:53.852
- <i>Are you there, Mrs. Nelson?
- Yes.</i>

14:54.060 --> 14:56.438
Needless to say, this is a
matter of great concern to us,

14:56.646 --> 14:57.989
and if it would not
be too much trouble,

14:58.189 --> 14:59.190
we would like you to come down

14:59.399 --> 15:03.029
tomorrow morning to 26 Federal Plaza.
Do you think you could do that?

15:03.277 --> 15:05.325
- I suppose so.
- About 9:00 a.m.?

15:06.614 --> 15:09.493
- Yes.
- Just ask for Agent Alonzo Mosely.

15:09.742 --> 15:12.370
Thanks for your cooperation.
Have a nice day.

15:29.720 --> 15:31.814
[phone dialing]

15:32.849 --> 15:34.101
[phone ringing]

15:34.308 --> 15:36.777
<i>- Hello?
- Dana? it's Helen.</i>

15:36.978 --> 15:38.025
<i>The FBI just called.</i>

15:38.229 --> 15:39.572
<i>They want to speak to me
about Jonathan.</i>

15:39.772 --> 15:43.322
<i>- Oh, my God! Helen.
- [Jonathan]: Helen, what's going on?</i>

15:43.526 --> 15:44.823
<i>[Helen]: Jonathan,
the FBI just called.</i>

15:45.027 --> 15:46.995
<i>They know we spoke the night
you were arrested.</i>

15:47.196 --> 15:49.449
<i>[Jonathan]: Hang up the phone, Helen.
Right now.</i>

15:49.949 --> 15:51.872
[tape rewinding]

15:52.076 --> 15:53.498
[phone dialing]

15:53.703 --> 15:55.376
Aah, sweet music.

15:56.456 --> 15:58.254
[car starting]

17:22.250 --> 17:24.469
[muffled conversation]

17:41.686 --> 17:43.484
[Go9 growls]

17:51.571 --> 17:54.415
[barking]

17:58.661 --> 18:02.086
[barking continues]

18:08.379 --> 18:10.302
- What is it, Jon?
- I don't know.

18:10.923 --> 18:13.017
Okay. Okay, Heidi. Okay.

18:14.260 --> 18:16.262
Alonzo Mosely, FBI!
You're under arrest!

18:16.470 --> 18:18.143
Get this fucking dog out of here!

18:18.347 --> 18:19.849
Get the dog out of here, ma'am!

18:20.057 --> 18:22.151
Not you. You stay there.
Get the dog, ma'am.

18:22.351 --> 18:23.603
- Do it, do it.
- Get the dog!

18:23.811 --> 18:25.563
Heidi. Come on, girl.
Come on, now.

18:25.771 --> 18:27.068
Good girl.
Come on, come on.

18:27.273 --> 18:29.742
Don't move or I'll shoot you
right through the glass.

18:35.865 --> 18:37.833
Get over here.
Put your hands up against the wall.

18:37.992 --> 18:40.836
Your hands up against the wall.
Spread your feet.

18:45.082 --> 18:47.176
Relax. There won't be a problem.

18:48.544 --> 18:50.717
Put your left hand behind your head.

18:51.255 --> 18:53.007
Put your left... That's it.

19:04.810 --> 19:06.778
You're taking me to the airport,
aren't you?

19:10.483 --> 19:12.781
You don't look
like an FBI agent to me.

19:14.236 --> 19:16.204
Yeah?
Well you don't look like a Duke to me.

19:17.031 --> 19:18.123
If you're an FBI agent,

19:18.324 --> 19:19.371
why don't you just take me
to the FBI office?

19:19.575 --> 19:23.546
If you don't be quiet, this is going
to be the worst trip of your life.

19:24.622 --> 19:26.420
You work for Jimmy Serrano,
don't you?

19:26.624 --> 19:28.126
I don't work for that
piece of shit.

19:28.334 --> 19:30.507
Your bail bondsman hired me
to bring you back to LA,

19:30.711 --> 19:31.712
and that's what I'm doing.

19:31.962 --> 19:33.839
- I got money, you know.
- I'm sure you do.

19:34.048 --> 19:36.676
- I'll give you whatever you want.
- Start by shutting up.

19:36.884 --> 19:39.728
I've known you all of two minutes,
and already I don't like you.

19:40.179 --> 19:42.432
Gee, that's too bad.
I really like you.

19:46.060 --> 19:48.233
I can't keep you cuffed
on a commercial flight.

19:48.437 --> 19:50.064
I gotta check my gun with my luggage,

19:50.272 --> 19:52.900
but you fuck with me once
and I'm gonna break your neck.

19:53.109 --> 19:54.452
- I can't fly.
- What?

19:54.652 --> 19:57.656
- You heard me. I can't fly.
- No, no. You're gonna have to do better than that, pal.

19:57.863 --> 20:00.787
No, I don't have to do better than that,
because it's the truth. I can't fly.

20:00.991 --> 20:02.789
- I suffer from aviophobia.
- What does that mean?

20:02.993 --> 20:06.463
It means I can't fly. I also suffer
from acrophobia and claustrophobia.

20:06.664 --> 20:08.507
Well, I'll tell you what.
If you don't cooperate,

20:08.708 --> 20:10.460
you're gonna suffer
from "fistophobia."

20:12.586 --> 20:14.930
[phone rings]

20:15.214 --> 20:16.932
Moscone's Bail Bonds.

20:17.216 --> 20:19.139
Jerry, put Eddie on the phone.

20:20.010 --> 20:21.478
Jack, what's the progress?

20:21.679 --> 20:22.805
- I got him.
- You got who?

20:23.013 --> 20:24.310
The Duke. He's standing right here.

20:24.557 --> 20:26.434
You got him? Already?

20:26.684 --> 20:28.277
<i>Sure do. Want to say hello?</i>

20:28.477 --> 20:30.730
Say hello to your bail bondsman,
Eddie Moscone.

