- Everything's under control.

36:57.424 --> 37:00.268
Take it easy. Alonzo Mosely, FBI.

37:00.468 --> 37:01.811
Radio ahead.
I want the local police

37:02.011 --> 37:03.729
at the next stop to place
this man under arrest.

37:03.930 --> 37:06.274
- What the fuck are you talkin' about?
- That's enough out of you!

37:06.474 --> 37:08.101
Go ahead.
Get on the horn and call the cops.

37:19.487 --> 37:20.739
Is this good news or bad news?

37:20.947 --> 37:22.199
Apparently Mardukas and Walsh

37:22.407 --> 37:24.205
are on the Amtrak
headed to Los Angeles.

37:24.409 --> 37:28.414
Another bounty hunter was arrested
after he tried to take Mardukas away.

37:28.663 --> 37:30.631
I want the jet ready in 20 minutes.

37:59.611 --> 38:02.581
- Where's Jack Walsh?
- He got off with the other guy...

38:02.781 --> 38:04.499
...two or three stops ago.

38:05.366 --> 38:06.993
His real name's Mosely.

38:07.410 --> 38:08.957
I'm Mosely!

38:13.208 --> 38:16.803
I want to make a collect call
to Eddie Moscone from Jack Walsh.

38:19.756 --> 38:23.181
- Moscone's Bail Bonds.
- Jerry, it's Jack. Put Eddie on.

38:23.510 --> 38:26.764
- Jesus, Jack! Where the hell have you been?
- Jack, I want to talk to him.

38:26.971 --> 38:27.813
Jack, where are you?

38:28.014 --> 38:29.641
Where am I?
Eddie, I want to ask you something.

38:29.849 --> 38:31.271
How come Dorfler wound up on my ass?

38:31.476 --> 38:33.319
Did you put him on this,
you son of a bitch?

38:33.520 --> 38:36.069
Wait a minute, wait a minute. Dorfler?
How could I put Dorfler on you?

38:36.272 --> 38:38.821
- I don't even know where the fuck you are.
- You had nothin' to do with it?

38:39.025 --> 38:40.698
Where are you?
You got the Duke or what?

38:40.902 --> 38:43.451
- You're damn right I got him.
- Where are you?

38:43.655 --> 38:47.159
<i>Where am I? I'm somewhere
between... I don't know. Toledo and Cleveland.</i>

38:47.367 --> 38:49.040
- We're gettin' on a bus.
- Bingo.

38:49.661 --> 38:52.289
Bus? What're you gonna do... Jack, don't get on a...
What, are you out of your mind?

38:52.497 --> 38:54.841
Will you just shut up for a minute
and listen to me? We're gettin' on a bus.

38:55.041 --> 38:57.464
<i>I just wanted to let you know
we're on our way, okay?</i>

38:57.669 --> 38:59.387
Don't hang UP!

38:59.671 --> 39:02.675
Shit! What the hell is this guy doin'?

39:02.924 --> 39:04.096
I don't know.

39:06.427 --> 39:07.724
Listen...

39:07.929 --> 39:09.897
Maybe I ought to get some donuts
or something, huh?

39:25.029 --> 39:27.452
Two one-way tickets
to Los Angeles, please.

39:28.700 --> 39:30.043
Still gonna make our schedule?

39:30.243 --> 39:32.371
Don't worry.
I'll get you there on time.

39:32.579 --> 39:33.922
Don't have any illusions.

39:34.289 --> 39:36.587
- Illusions?
- Illusions.

39:36.749 --> 39:38.171
Illusions.

39:38.376 --> 39:41.129
I'm sorry, sir.
This card's been canceled.

39:41.129 --> 39:43.177
Huh?
Has it been canceled?

39:43.423 --> 39:45.425
I'm sorry, that's a mistake.
Would you please try it again?

39:45.633 --> 39:47.931
- I checked it twice, sir.
- Please try it again.

39:48.136 --> 39:49.638
Please try it again.

39:49.846 --> 39:51.564
- Did you pay the bill?
- Shut up.

39:51.764 --> 39:53.357
I'm sorry, sir. It's been canceled.

39:53.600 --> 39:57.104
Ma'am, that is impossible. I pay my bills.
There is no way that that could be canceled.

39:57.312 --> 39:59.155
- It's been canceled.
- Shut up!

39:59.355 --> 40:00.732
- Please.
- It's canceled, sir.

40:00.940 --> 40:03.910
- Would you like to try another credit card?
- I don't have any other credit cards.

40:04.110 --> 40:06.329
- Or cash.
- Please, would you just try that again?

40:06.529 --> 40:07.872
- No.
- All right.

40:09.449 --> 40:11.292
Alonzo... Jack Walsh.

40:11.659 --> 40:13.081
Federal Bureau of investigation.

40:13.286 --> 40:15.789
This is an official business.
I'm taking this man and he's in my custody.

40:15.997 --> 40:19.171
I'm taking him to Los Angeles, okay?
So please try this once more.

40:20.543 --> 40:23.171
Jack Walsh is not the name
on that badge, sir.

40:26.007 --> 40:28.180
Would you like me to call the FBI?

40:30.094 --> 40:31.937
Or would you like to pay cash?

40:34.349 --> 40:38.274
- How much is it?
- $264 for two tickets.

40:38.478 --> 40:39.900
$264.

40:40.104 --> 40:41.526
Here's $100.

40:47.195 --> 40:49.448
- Got any money on you?
- A lot.

40:56.579 --> 40:58.377
You call that a lot of money?

40:58.581 --> 41:00.675
It's enough to get you
where I'm gonna get you.

41:03.002 --> 41:07.052
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven.

41:07.256 --> 41:09.679
Got the whole fuckin' force after me, huh?

41:09.676 --> 41:10.723
[laughs]

41:26.901 --> 41:28.448
Who the fuck are you?

41:28.903 --> 41:30.826
Special Agent Mosely, FBI.

41:31.406 --> 41:33.249
Oh, goddamn it! I didn't do anything.

41:33.491 --> 41:35.869
Relax. Just want to ask you
a few questions, that's all.

41:36.077 --> 41:38.250
Yeah. Fucking A. Help yourself.

41:51.175 --> 41:53.519
So what do you know about Jack Walsh?

41:57.724 --> 42:00.728
Oh, no, no. Come on, come on.
Cigarettes are killers.

42:01.644 --> 42:02.566
So are women.

42:02.770 --> 42:06.024
Not the right woman. My wife
and I have a wonderful relationship.

42:06.232 --> 42:07.324
She's stuck it out with me
through all of this.

42:07.483 --> 42:10.453
Stuck it out with you and
all your millions, what a trooper.

42:10.653 --> 42:13.827
I don't have millions, Jack.
I gave it all to charity, remember?

42:14.032 --> 42:16.330
You didn't keep
just a little for yourself, Jon?

42:16.325 --> 42:18.373
I kept enough to get away
and stay hidden.

42:18.369 --> 42:19.291
Yeah, right.

42:20.538 --> 42:23.212
You know, when we change buses in Chicago
you're gonna have a couple hours.

42:23.458 --> 42:24.675
I think you'd be a better man

42:24.876 --> 42:26.799
if you used that time to
look up your ex-wife and daughter.

42:27.003 --> 42:28.505
It's a perfect opportunity.

42:28.713 --> 42:30.886
Why don't you mind your own business?

42:35.428 --> 42:38.056
Let me ask you this: Why is it you
haven't seen them in nine years?

42:38.264 --> 42:39.516
- Why?
- Yeah.

42:39.724 --> 42:41.351
Just to get you off my back
I'll tell you why.

42:41.559 --> 42:43.106
She married a police lieutenant

42:43.311 --> 42:45.313
and I'm not very popular
with the Chicago Police Department.

42:45.563 --> 42:48.282
- Why aren't you popular with them?
- That's a whole other...

42:48.483 --> 42:50.281
Do we know each other?

42:50.943 --> 42:52.320
- Why?
- Why?

42:53.154 --> 42:54.451
What did you do?

42:55.239 --> 42:57.287
Why aren't you popular
with the Chicago Police?

42:57.492 --> 42:59.745
That's something that
really doesn't concern you.

42:59.952 --> 43:02.455
- Did she hurt you, Jack?
- Yeah.

43:03.664 --> 43:06.087
- I'm sorry.
- What are you sorry about?

43:06.292 --> 43:08.545
- I'm sorry you're hurt.
- I'm not hurt.

43:09.295 --> 43:10.968
- You just said you were hurt.
- I'm not hurt.

43:11.172 --> 43:13.721
- You just said you were hurt.
- I didn't say I was hurt. You said I was hurt.

43:13.925 --> 43:15.768
I asked you if you were hurt
and you said, "Yeah, I'm hurt."

43:15.968 --> 43:17.220
That's because you made me say it.

43:17.428 --> 43:18.896
You're startin'
to put words in my mouth.

43:19.097 --> 43:21.520
Jack, you're a grown man.
You have control over your own words.

43:21.724 --> 43:22.941
You're goddamn right I do.

43:23.101 --> 43:25.399
So here come two words for you:
Shut the fuck up!

43:29.148 --> 43:30.741
Excuse me.

43:30.942 --> 43:33.036
Walsh called Moscone about
a half an hour ago

43:33.194 --> 43:34.411
from outside Toledo.

43:34.612 --> 43:39.038
He's on an interstate Coach Lines bus
headed for Chicago.

43:44.163 --> 43:45.380
Come on.

43:46.082 --> 43:48.255
Sir, what do we do with this guy?

43:48.960 --> 43:50.883
Let him go.

43:55.675 --> 43:58.144
Son of a bitch stole my cigarettes.

43:58.803 --> 44:01.272
When's the last time
you had a chest X-ray?

44:04.016 --> 44:05.893
You know about secondary smoke?

44:06.102 --> 44:08.070
You could give people lung cancer

44:08.271 --> 44:11.275
who are innocent
and trying to live healthy lives.

44:11.607 --> 44:15.032
Why don't you just go back to sleep?
Leave me alone.

44:15.278 --> 44:17.656
- Do whatever you have to do.
- Put the cigarette out.

44:17.864 --> 44:19.787
Why don't you shut up
and leave me alone?

44:19.991 --> 44:21.834
Put the cigarette out, Jack.

44:24.328 --> 44:26.171
Put the cigarette out.

44:26.747 --> 44:28.920
What a pain in the ass this guy is.

44:29.375 --> 44:30.672
Thank you, thank you.

44:30.877 --> 44:34.381
- I thought you were putting it out.
- No, I'm not putting it out.

44:34.881 --> 44:37.760
Why aren't you popular
with the Chicago Police Department?

44:39.802 --> 44:41.725
Sid's downstairs.

44:46.475 --> 44:48.648
- What's up?
- I think you and I should talk.

44:48.853 --> 44:50.605
Why are you hangin' around for?
Take a walk.

44:50.813 --> 44:52.486
I heard somebody picked up Mardukas
in New York.

44:52.648 --> 44:54.901
- It's old news, Sidney. I'm already on it.
- I don't have to tell you

44:55.109 --> 44:56.486
<i>what)“ happen if he becomes
a government witness.</i>

44:56.694 --> 44:58.071
I can assure you that
will not be the case.

44:58.279 --> 45:00.452
I assumed you were
taking that position

45:00.656 --> 45:02.624
but I am supposed to advise you
against such action.

45:02.825 --> 45:04.327
Sidney, relax.
Have a cream soda.

45:04.535 --> 45:06.879
Everything is gonna be
all over within a few minutes.

45:40.988 --> 45:43.241
[sirens wailing]

45:49.121 --> 45:50.919
Who the fuck are these guys?

45:52.124 --> 45:53.671
Hands on the bus!

45:58.923 --> 46:00.550
All right, spread 'em.

46:06.847 --> 46:08.474
It's the fuckin' feds.

46:10.351 --> 46:11.944
Remember me?

46:13.938 --> 46:15.656
Agent Foster Grant.

46:15.856 --> 46:18.359
Alonzo, aren't you gonna thank me
for doin' your job for you?

46:20.736 --> 46:22.409
Thank you, Walsh.

46:22.613 --> 46:24.411
[gunshots]

46:31.580 --> 46:32.957
Let's get the fuck out of here!
Come on!

46:50.016 --> 46:52.485
- What the hell are you doing?
- Keep moving.

46:53.102 --> 46:55.696
What? No, no!

47:00.860 --> 47:05.206
Wait a minute. Jesus Christ!
All right, I'm comin'!

47:05.448 --> 47:08.327
- Come on!
- All right! Wait a minute!

47:10.411 --> 47:13.335
Walsh, you son of a bitch!

47:22.840 --> 47:24.513
- My God, my God!
- Shut up.

47:24.717 --> 47:26.094
- What the hell was that?
- Shut up.

47:26.302 --> 47:28.725
- Why were they shooting?
- Those are Serrano's people back there.

47:28.929 --> 47:30.852
They're not even waiting
for you to get to jail.

47:31.057 --> 47:33.651
You're turnin' me in.
Why are we runnin' away from the FBI?

47:33.851 --> 47:36.525
'Cause I gotta bring you back myself,
otherwise I won't get my money.

47:36.729 --> 47:38.026
I won't give you to the feds.

47:40.066 --> 47:42.660
"Alonzo Mosely."
Isn't that the name you've been using?

47:42.860 --> 47:44.282
Let me see that.

47:47.365 --> 47:49.333
- Look at this wealth of information.
- What?

47:49.533 --> 47:51.706
They got a tap on Moscone's line.

47:53.621 --> 47:55.043
Son of a bitch!

47:56.957 --> 47:59.631
What are you doin'?
What are you doin'?

48:01.295 --> 48:04.265
How far do you think we're
gonna get in a stolen FBI car?

48:06.967 --> 48:08.139
What's that for?

48:08.344 --> 48:10.563
An inside joke between me and Alonzo.

48:11.430 --> 48:13.979
- Tony Darvo, line one.
- Yeah?

48:14.183 --> 48:16.060
Sorry, Jimmy. It didn't happen.

48:17.103 --> 48:18.901
It didn't happen?
Say that again, Tony?

48:19.105 --> 48:20.106
<i>It just didn't happen.</i>

48:20.314 --> 48:21.861
I mean, there were cops all over the place.

48:22.066 --> 48:23.864
There were a million
fuckin' feds all over.

48:24.026 --> 48:25.869
Jimmy, it was... it was a mess.

48:26.028 --> 48:27.996
- It was a real mess.
- You'd better get off the line, Jimmy.

48:28.239 --> 48:31.834
- If they've got a tap on that line--
- Sidney, shut your fucking mouth!

48:32.993 --> 48:34.336
Now listen to me, dummy.

48:34.537 --> 48:37.040
Do they have Mardukas
in custody or not?

48:37.039 --> 48:38.006
I don't, I don't, I don't know.

48:38.207 --> 48:40.335
Jimmy, I don't know. The cops
are swarming all over the place.

48:40.584 --> 48:41.836
<i>We couldn't see anything.</i>

48:42.002 --> 48:44.004
Let me tell you two stupid
motherfuckers something.

48:44.213 --> 48:46.716
I don't want to get another
phone call like this, because

48:46.924 --> 48:50.053
if I do I'll get on a fuckin' plane,
and I'm gonna blowtorch the both of you.

48:50.261 --> 48:51.683
Do you understand?

48:52.138 --> 48:53.640
Are you gonna stop? I'm on the phone!

48:53.848 --> 48:55.225
I'm talking to Jimmy.
What are you doin'?

48:55.766 --> 48:58.315
I should've killed Walsh
in Chicago a long time ago.

48:58.686 --> 49:01.280
Don't say a word to me, Sidney.
Don't say a fuckin' word to me.

49:01.480 --> 49:04.074
I'll get up and I'll bury
this telephone in your head.

49:29.842 --> 49:30.843
I can't believe this.

49:31.051 --> 49:34.225
I haven't seen either of them in nine years
and the first thing outta my mouth is gonna be:

49:34.430 --> 49:36.432
"Can I borrow a few hundred bucks?"

49:36.640 --> 49:39.610
I have a feeling this is going
to be very good for you.

49:47.109 --> 49:48.952
[bell rings]

49:52.490 --> 49:54.333
You look fine.

49:58.746 --> 50:00.168
<i>Who are you Ql-“ls?</i>

50:01.040 --> 50:03.042
I'm your mother's ex-husband.

50:05.085 --> 50:08.305
- Mom!
- Nice kid.

50:18.349 --> 50:19.646
Hi, Gail.

50:20.226 --> 50:22.069
- Hello.
- How're you doin'?

50:22.645 --> 50:24.022
I'm doin' good.

50:28.651 --> 50:29.618
Hi.

50:30.736 --> 50:32.704
They mentioned you and him
on the news this morning.

50:32.905 --> 50:34.282
- They did?
- Yeah.

50:35.449 --> 50:37.372
What did they say? Anything good?

50:37.576 --> 50:39.294
[chuckles]

50:39.453 --> 50:42.332
No. Are you all right?

50:43.040 --> 50:44.337
Yeah.

50:45.626 --> 50:47.799
You're in a lot of trouble, Jack.

50:49.588 --> 50:51.886
Can I come in for a few minutes, Gail?

50:54.009 --> 50:56.057
Can I come in for a few minutes?

50:57.596 --> 50:59.348
Yeah.

51:02.142 --> 51:03.109
I won't stay long.

51:03.310 --> 51:05.859
I just need to borrow
some money to get to LA.

51:06.397 --> 51:08.024
You know I'm good for it.

51:08.816 --> 51:11.535
Jack, I don't think I have
that kind of cash in the house.

51:11.735 --> 51:15.581
I'm so embarrassed.
I'm just in a jam, Gail.

51:17.783 --> 51:19.330
You look beautiful.

51:20.286 --> 51:22.209
You don't look much like a criminal.

51:22.413 --> 51:23.630
I'm a white-collar criminal.

51:23.831 --> 51:25.458
Jason, go upstairs now.

51:29.253 --> 51:30.755
Jack, you shouldn't be here.

51:31.046 --> 51:33.720
If Ted comes home,
he's gonna arrest you and him.

51:33.924 --> 51:35.767
- Arrest us?
- Yeah.

51:36.969 --> 51:40.189
Then we'd really be in a lot of trouble 'cause
I'm afraid I'm a little short of bribe money.

51:40.389 --> 51:42.892
All right, Jack, don't start.
Please, don't.

51:43.100 --> 51:45.228
How is Lieutenant
whatever-his-name-is?

51:45.436 --> 51:48.064
- It's captain now.
- Captain? Royalty.

51:48.272 --> 51:50.866
Jack, I don't want any trouble.
Do you understand that?

51:51.066 --> 51:53.569
Please, it is not a good day for this.
I mean it.

51:53.777 --> 51:55.199
I'm sorry that my fugitive timetable

51:55.404 --> 51:57.406
doesn't coincide
with your social calendar.

51:57.615 --> 51:59.743
- I don't think she was saying that.
- Stay out of this, Jon.

51:59.950 --> 52:00.621
Alright, same old Jack,

52:00.826 --> 52:03.955
you get your feelings hurt and then you
just walk around and hurt everybody else.

52:03.954 --> 52:05.251
The last thing I need now is one of your lectures!

52:05.247 --> 52:06.965
I'm not lecturing you, stupid!
I'm trying to protect you!

52:07.207 --> 52:09.335
- Come on!
- Ted is gonna be home any minute.

52:09.543 --> 52:11.386
We're all going out.
It's an important night for us.

52:11.879 --> 52:13.802
Important night? What's so important
about tonight? Wait, let me guess.

52:14.006 --> 52:16.555
- What is it, payoff night?
- Alright, that's it! Get out!

52:16.759 --> 52:19.933
- Let's not fight.
- Gail, listen! I'm in a big fuckin' jam!

52:19.928 --> 52:22.056
I just need to borrow some money
so I can get this guy back to LA

52:22.264 --> 52:24.016
and I'm out of this
miserable fucking business forever!

52:24.266 --> 52:26.018
Can't you understand that?

52:44.286 --> 52:45.458
Hi.

52:48.415 --> 52:49.917
Denise?

52:54.630 --> 52:56.428
You got so big.

53:13.107 --> 53:15.951
- I'm sorry. I'm gonna go now. I'm sorry.
- No, hold on.

53:22.533 --> 53:25.662
I'm sorry, honey.
It's just, we're havin' a...

53:34.044 --> 53:35.762
What grade are you in now?

53:35.921 --> 53:36.888
Eighth.

53:37.089 --> 53:38.887
Are you in the eighth grade?

53:59.737 --> 54:03.458
Here's $40. That's all I've got,
but these are the keys to my car.

54:03.657 --> 54:05.330
It's the station wagon
in the driveway.

54:05.534 --> 54:08.037
- I'll tell Ted that it's in the shop.
- Okay.

54:08.287 --> 54:11.166
And we'll worry about it
when you get back to LA.

54:12.291 --> 54:14.339
So, does he take good care of you?

54:17.588 --> 54:20.011
Yeah?
Well, that's all I wanted to know.

54:21.425 --> 54:23.519
So what's he gonna say about this?

54:24.762 --> 54:28.357
- He'll understand.
- Yeah, that's love, y'know?

54:29.975 --> 54:31.602
Bye, honey.

55:09.306 --> 55:10.649
Wait.

55:11.475 --> 55:13.944
It isn't much.
About $180 babysitting money.

55:14.144 --> 55:16.192
- Sweetheart, I can't.
- Take it.

55:16.396 --> 55:18.569
- I can't.
- Please.

55:20.108 --> 55:22.327
- Take it.
- I can't, sweetheart.

55:56.270 --> 56:00.571
Hello. I'd like to make a collect call
to an Eddie Moscone from a Jack Walsh.

56:00.983 --> 56:03.782
[phone rings]

56:04.069 --> 56:05.446
Moscone's Bail Bonds.

56:05.654 --> 56:07.201
Jerry, Jack, put Eddie on the phone.

56:07.573 --> 56:08.950
Eddie, it's Jack.

56:09.491 --> 56:11.414
Jack, stop fuckin' around.
Where are you?

56:11.618 --> 56:14.041
Where am I? I'm in Boise, Idaho.

56:14.371 --> 56:16.590
No,no, no, wait a minute.
I'm in Anchorage, Alaska.

56:16.832 --> 56:19.051
No, no, no, wait.
I'm in Casper, Wyoming.

56:19.293 --> 56:22.638
I'm in the lobby of a Howard Johnson's
and I'm wearing a pink carnation.

56:22.838 --> 56:24.681
What the fuck
are you talkin' about?

56:24.882 --> 56:27.180
I'm not talkin' to you.
I'm talkin' to the other guys.

56:27.426 --> 56:28.552
What other guys?

56:28.760 --> 56:31.434
Let me describe the scene to you.
There's these guys, see.

56:31.638 --> 56:33.311
They've probably been up
for like two days.

56:33.515 --> 56:35.734
They stink of B.0.
They have coffee breath.

56:35.976 --> 56:38.855
They're constipated from sitting
on their asses for so long.

56:39.104 --> 56:41.106
They're sitting in a van
and they're probably parked

56:41.315 --> 56:42.737
right up the street
from your office.

